Controladora Vuela Compañía de Aviación, S.A.B. de C.V.: Private Company Information - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 28, 2017 6:06 AM ET
Airlines

Company Overview of Controladora Vuela Compañía de Aviación, S.A.B. de C.V.



Snapshot People




Company Overview
Controladora Vuela Compañía de Aviación, S.A.B. de C.V. provides air transportation services for passengers, cargo, and mail in Mexico and internationally. As of December 31, 2016, the company operated a fleet of 69 Airbus narrow-body aircraft, which include 15 Airbus A319s, 44 A320s, and 10 A321s. It operates approximately 302 daily flights on routes that connect 40 cities in Mexico and 22 cities in the United States and Central America. The company also offers recruitment and payroll, and merchandising services. Controladora Vuela Compañía de Aviación, S.A.B. de C.V. was founded in 2003 and is headquartered in Mexico City, Mexico.


Tower B13th FloorAvenida Antonio Dovalí Jaime No. 70Colonia Zedec Santa FeMexico City, DF 01210MexicoFounded in 20034,948 Employees



Phone: 52 55 5261 6400

www.volaris.com







Key Executives for Controladora Vuela Compañía de Aviación, S.A.B. de C.V.


Controladora Vuela Compañía de Aviación, S.A.B. de C.V. does not have any Key Executives recorded. 



Controladora Vuela Compañía de Aviación, S.A.B. de C.V. Key Developments

Controladora Vuela Compañía De Aviación, S.A.B. De C.V. Announces Unaudited Consolidated Earnings and Operating Results for the Second Quarter and Six Months Ended June 30, 2017; Provides Earnings Guidance for the Third Quarter of 2017; Provides Production Guidance for the Production Third Quarter and Full Year 2017
Jul 21 17
Controladora Vuela Compañía de Aviación, S.A.B. de C.V. announced unaudited consolidated earnings and operating results for the second quarter and six months ended June 30, 2017. For the quarter, total operating revenues were MXN 5,982 million against MXN 5,131 million a year ago. Operating income was MXN 39 million against MXN 388 million a year ago. Loss before income tax was MXN 520 million against income of MXN 1,323 million a year ago. Net loss was MXN 520 million against income of MXN 935 million a year ago. Basic and diluted LPS was MXN 0.51 pesos against EPS of MXN 0.92 pesos a year ago. Basic and diluted LPS per ADS were MXN 5.14 pesos against EPS of MXN 9.24 pesos a year ago. LBITDA was MXN 380 million against EBITDA of MXN 1,449 million a year ago. Adjusted EBITDA was MXN 178 million against MXN 526 million a year ago. Adjusted EBITDAR was MXN 1,556 million against MXN 1,819 million a year ago. Net cash flow used in operating activities was MXN 215 million against net cash flow provided by operating activities of MXN 194 million a year ago.

For the six-month period, the company reported total operating revenues were MXN 11,637 million against MXN 10,313 million a year ago. Operating loss was MXN 733 million against income of MXN 1,224 million a year ago. Loss before income tax was MXN 2,436 million against income of MXN 2,195 million a year ago. Net loss was MXN 1,881 million against income of MXN 1,536 million a year ago. Basic and diluted LPS were MXN 1.86 pesos against EPS of MXN 1.52 pesos a year ago. Basic and diluted LPS per ADS were MXN 18.59 pesos against EPS of MXN 15.18 pesos a year ago. LBITDA was MXN 2,169 million against EBITDA of MXN 2,414 million a year ago. Adjusted LBITDA was MXN 466 million against EBITDA of MXN 1,482 million a year ago. Adjusted EBITDAR was MXN 2,611 million against MXN 3,994 million a year ago. Net cash flow provided by operating activities was MXN 254 million against MXN 1,523 million a year ago.

For the quarter, Available seat miles (ASMs) were MXN 4,639 million against MXN 3,980 million a year ago. Revenue passenger miles (RPMs) were MXN 3,973 million against MXN 3,428 million a year ago. Load factor was 85.7% against 86.1% a year ago. 

For the six-month period, the company reported available seat miles (ASMs) was MXN 9,186 million against MXN 7,872 million a year ago. Revenue passenger miles (RPMs) were MXN 7,756 million against MXN 6,735 million a year ago. Load factor was 84.5% against 85.6% a year ago.



For the third quarter, the company expects to grow ASMs in the 9% to 11% range, broken down by 7% to 9% domestic growth and 13% to 15% international growth. 

For the full year 2017, the company foresee a full year ASM growth in the range of 13% to 14% year-over-year


For the third quarter, the company expects to achieve an adjusted EBITDAR margin in the range of low to mid-30s, assuming current spot exchange rate and jet fuel prices. Aircraft and engine rental expense for the third quarter is expected to be in the order of $80 million.


Volaris Reports Preliminary Traffic Results for the Month and Year-To-Date Ended June 2017
Jul 10 17
Volaris reported preliminary traffic results for the month and year-to-date ended June 2017. During June 2017, the company increased total capacity, as measured in Available Seat Miles (ASMs), by 7.8% year over year. Total demand, as measured in Revenue Passenger Miles (RPMs), in June 2017 increased 8.0% year over year, reaching 1.3 billion. Volaris transported a total of 1.3 million passengers during the month, an increase of 3.7% year over year. Network load factor for June was 89.1%, an increase of 0.2 percentage points year over year. 

During the first six months of 2017, the company increased total capacity, as measured in Available Seat Miles (ASMs), by 16.7% year over year. Total demand, as measured in Revenue Passenger Miles (RPMs), for the six months ended June 2017 increased 15.2% year over year, reaching 7.8 billion. Volaris transported a total of 8.0 million passengers during the first six months of 2017, an increase of 13.5% year over year. Network load factor for the first six months of the year was 84.5%, a decrease of 1.1 percentage points year over year.


Controladora Vuela Compañía de Aviación, S.A.B. de C.V. to Report Q2, 2017 Results on Jul 21, 2017
Jun 22 17
Controladora Vuela Compañía de Aviación, S.A.B. de C.V. announced that they will report Q2, 2017 results at 9:00 AM, Central Standard Time (Mexico) on Jul 21, 2017


